    <note type="biography">
        <p>French geologist. Studied the geology of France and Austria. Collaborated with Charles Lyell in comparing the Tertiary and Secondary strata on both sides of the English Channel, 1823–4. A founder of the Société géologique de France, 1830; president, 1834, 1839, and 1851. Professor of geology, the Sorbonne, 1831.</p></note>
